      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
        "old_string": "In Prometheus, trace management is centralized in `tracing/tracing.go` with the `Manager` type. The `Run()` method (line 62) registers the global TextMapPropagator as `propagation.TraceContext{}`. For client-side propagation, `storage/remote/client.go` wraps HTTP transports with `otelhttp.NewTransport()` for both read (line 161) and write (line 223) clients, with optional client trace instrumentation using `otelhttptrace`. The `web/web.go` file uses `otelhttp.NewHandler()` to wrap HTTP handlers with tracing support. All three projects standardize on OpenTelemetry's W3C TraceContext propagator for inter-service trace context correlation.\"",
        "new_string": "In Prometheus, trace management is centralized in `tracing/tracing.go` with the `Manager` type. The `Run()` method (line 62) registers the global TextMapPropagator as `propagation.TraceContext{}`. For client-side propagation, `storage/remote/client.go` wraps HTTP transports with `otelhttp.NewTransport()` for both read (line 161) and write (line 223) clients, with optional client trace instrumentation using `otelhttptrace`. The `scrape/scrape.go` file also applies `otelhttp.NewTransport()` to scrape job HTTP clients (line 2265), enabling trace context propagation to metrics targets. The `web/web.go` file uses `otelhttp.NewHandler()` to wrap HTTP handlers with tracing support. All three projects standardize on OpenTelemetry's W3C TraceContext propagator for inter-service trace context correlation.\"",
